SIMPLE: stiffening
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stiffening
<hw>Stiff"en*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act or process of
making stiff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something used to make anything stiff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stiffening order</b></col> <fld>(Com.)</fld>, <cd>a
permission granted by the customs department to take cargo or ballast on
board before the old cargo is out, in order to steady the
ship.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiff-hearted</ent>⟦br⟧
